 <item> <title>The Coming Crossroads in Higher Education</title>
 <link>https://www.ed.gov/news/speeches/coming-crossroads-higher-education</link>
 <description>It is a pleasure to join you today to speak about the nation’s higher education agenda.

Before I begin my formal remarks, let me say that  there is a lot going on right now on Capitol Hill. Because Congress has failed  to agree on a solution, interest rates on new subsidized student loans doubled  on July 1, costing seven million students an average of $1,000.</description>
